{"title_page": "Adanga Maru", "text_new": "{{short description|2018 Indian Tamil-language action thriller film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Adanga Maru\n| image          = Adanga Maru.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = Karthik Thangavel\n| writer         = \n| screenplay     = Karthik Thangavel\n| story          = Karthik Thangavel\n| studio         = Home Movie Makers\n| starring       = [[Jayam Ravi]]<br />[[Raashi Khanna]]\n| music          = [[Sam C. S.]]\n| distributor    = [[Clap Board Production]]\n| released       = 21 December 2018\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| producer       = Sujatha Vijaykumar\n| editing        = [[Anthony L. Ruben|Ruben]]\n| cinematography = [[Sathyan Sooryan]]\n| runtime        = 146 minutes\n| budget         = <!--Must cite a reliable published source with a reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb. no fan-sites.--> \n| gross          = <!--Must cite a reliable published source with a reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb. no fan-sites.--> \n}}\n'''''Adanga Maru''''' ({{trans|Refuse to bow down}}) is a 2018 Indian [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-language [[action film|action]] [[thriller film]] written and directed by Karthik Thangavel in his directorial debut. The film stars [[Jayam Ravi]] and [[Raashi Khanna]] with [[Ponvannan]], [[Ramdoss]], [[Sampath Raj]], [[Mime Gopi]], and [[Azhagam Perumal]] in supporting roles. The score and soundtrack was composed by [[Sam C. S.]], while cinematography and editing was handled by [[Sathyan Sooryan]] and [[Anthony L. Ruben]] respectively. The film began production in December 2017 and released on 21 December 2018.\n\n== Plot ==\nSubhash is an sincere and new Sub-Inspector of Police in Chennai. He resides with his father, mother, elder brother, his wife, and their twin daughters. He is all set to marry his fianc\u00e9e Anitha. He is new to his job and is assisted by Constable Ramadass and SSI Chandran. Subhash cannot stand the suffering of the public and looks for ways to better their lives, and this often lands him in trouble with his superior Inspector Muthukaruppan.\n\nOne day, Chandran and Subhash are called on to investigate the supposed suicide of a girl. On closer investigation, Subhash deduces that it was not a suicide and that she was murdered. While collecting evidence to support this, he comes across a person called Abhijit (Bharath Raj), whose cell number was active near the place. On confronting Abhijit and his friends Christy, Bhuvanesh, and Deepak, they reveal that they are all stoners from affluent families and show a video of them doing drugs, raping and murdering the girl and many other women, as well. Subhash gets enraged, beats them up, and locks them in jail. When his superior, a corrupt Joint Commissioner Saarangan IPS, asks for the proof behind his accusations, he finds out that the phone had automatically deleted all the video files just as he was trying to unlock it. The four are released due to lack of evidence and the influence of their respective fathers and Subhash is suspended. Abhijit and his friends vow revenge and soon enough, when Subhash goes home, he finds his parents and brother's family dead. Only one of his nieces, Anusha, is left alive. Meanwhile, Saarangan is bribed with a Porsche car and reports the murder of Subhash's family as a fire accident at their new house. Dejected at his powerlessness even though he is a police officer, Subhash resigns and threatens Saarangan that he will avenge his family's death and will make sure that the four guys die mercilessly at the hands of their own fathers.\n\nFirst, he kidnaps Bhuvan and locks him in a car with a mechanism that fills silane gas in it if anyone tries to open the door. Bhuvan's father, the district collector, accidentally opens the car door as he searches for his missing son, and Bhuvan is burnt alive in front of his father. Next, he kidnaps Deepak and Christy and keeps them at undisclosed locations. The police, in order to find the missing guys, try to unofficially arrest Subhash at gunpoint, but he triggers Muthukaruppan's pistol on purpose, resulting in his arrest and gaining unwanted public attention. With increasing media and political attention, Saarangan and the rich fathers are unable to carry out extreme measures of interrogation on Subhash, though he is in custody. Subhash then reveals to all of them that he kept Christy in a van and asks him to go to the airport, but Christy's father double crosses Subhash and asks him to run for help, thinking that Christy is safe when police and the public are nearby. Before Christy could do so, an auto-loaded gun in his bag starts beeping, and Christy, assumed to be a terrorist, is brutally shot and killed by the Paramilitary Force (CISF) soldiers to safeguard the public. After this, Deepak is found to be locked in a glass tank connected to harmful chemicals. Subhash and his tech friend expose him as a rapist to the public via an online gaming link, where the public can virtually try to shoot at Deepak in order to release the chemicals into the tank and eventually kill him. His father hires hackers to stop this, and when Deepak's location is found, he goes there and breaks open the tank to release him, but the chemicals instantly blow up, and he is killed. Meanwhile, Subhash also threatens Saarangan to check on his teenage daughter's safety. Saarangan panics but is relieved when she is found to be safe. Saarangan realizes his mistake and decides to support Subhash in his fight for justice to the rape and murder victims.\n\nNow that only Abhijit is left, his father Sanjay, a business tycoon, decides to release Subhash from custody and deal with him alone. Subhash tactfully kidnaps Abhijit and has him hanging on a rope. He also threatens to upload the video evidence online and expose their crimes, thereby bringing Sanjay's business empire down. He gives Sanjay an ultimatum that he could either hold on to the rope and save his son or let go and shut down the laptop instead, to save his reputation. In the end, the power-hungry Sanjay decides to save his reputation and lets go of the rope, killing Abhijit.\n\nOne year later, Subhash has become a peace-loving IPS officer, who murders criminals out of record to serve justice.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n*[[Jayam Ravi]] as S. Subash\n*[[Raashi Khanna]] as Anitha\n*[[Sampath Raj]] as J. C. P. Sarangan\n*[[Ramdoss]] as Constable Ramadass\n*[[Ponvannan]] as Subash's father\n*[[Azhagam Perumal]] as SI Chandran\n*[[Mime Gopi]] as Inspector Muthukarappan\n*Bharat Raj as Abhijit\n*Rajaa as Christy\n*[[Shabeer Kallarakkal]] as Bhuvanesh (Bhuvan)\n*[[Sriranjini (Tamil actress)|Sriranjini]] as Subash's mother\n*[[Subbu Panchu]] as Subash's brother\n*[[Meera Vasudevan]] as Subash's sister-in-law\n*[[Babu Antony]] as Sanjay, Abhijit's father\n*Dithi as Anusha\n*Dishi as Vinusha\n*[[Chaams]] as Drunkard\n*[[Shamna Kasim|Poorna]] as Subash's lawyer (guest appearance)<ref name=\"indiatimes\">{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/poorna-is-a-lawyer-in-adanga-maru/articleshow/65307050.cms|title=Poorna is a lawyer in Adanga Maru &#124; Tamil Movie News|website=Times of India|accessdate=31 October 2018}}</ref>\n*Mathew Varghese as a rich man\n*RJ Sindhu (special appearance in the song \"Aangu Vaangu\")\n*VJ Syed (special appearance in the song \"Aangu Vaangu\")\n{{colend}}\n\n== Production ==\nIn December 2017, Jayam Ravi announced on social media that his 23rd film will be an action-thriller titled ''Adanga Maru'' by debutant Karthik Thangavel.<ref name=\"firstpost\">{{cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/adanga-maru-jayam-ravi-announces-title-of-his-next-film-will-go-on-floors-on-14-december-4257997.html|title=Adanga Maru: Jayam Ravi announces title of his next film, will go on floors on 14 December- Entertainment News, Firstpost|website=firstpost.com|accessdate=31 October 2018|date=14 December 2017}}</ref> Stunt choreographer [[Stun Siva]]'s son, Kevin Kumar made his debut as stunt choreographer with this film.<ref name=\"indiatimes2\">{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/stun-sivas-son-gets-his-own-fight-sequence/articleshow/65164764.cms|title=Stun Siva's son gets his own fight sequence &#124; Tamil Movie News|website=Times of India|accessdate=31 October 2018}}</ref> Filming was completed in May 2018.<ref name=\"indiatimes3\">{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/jayam-ravis-adanga-maru-is-almost-complete/articleshow/64260440.cms|title=Jayam Ravi's 'Adanga Maru' is almost complete &#124; Tamil Movie News|website=Times of India|accessdate=31 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Soundtrack ==\nThe soundtrack was composed by [[Sam C. S.]]<ref name=\"saavn\">{{cite web|url=https://www.saavn.com/album/adanga-maru/SEe-AFCXq9Y_|title=Adanga Maru - All Songs - Download or Listen Free Online|website=Saavn|accessdate=31 October 2018}}</ref> The Audio Rights was bagged by [[Sony Music India|Sony Music]] in end of August 2018.\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Adanga Maru\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Sam C. S.]]\n| cover      = \n| alt        =\n| released   = 2018\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = Tamil\n| length     = 17:34\n| language   = Tamil\n| label      = [[Sony Music India|Sony Music]]\n| producer   = Sam C. S.\n| prev_title = [[Lakshmi (2018 film)|Lakshmi]]\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| next_title = [[Vanjagar Ulagam]]\n| next_year  = 2018\n}}\n{{tracklist\n| extra_column =Singers\n| title1 = Aangu Vaangu\n| extra1 = Sam C. S., Mukesh, [[M. L. R. Karthikeyan]]\n| length1 = 4:26\n| title2 = Saayaali\n| extra2 = Sathyaprakash, [[Chinmayi]]\n| length2 = 5:15\n| title3 = Pachai Dhrogangal\n| extra3 = [[Haricharan]]\n| length3 = 3:46\n| title4 = Kaar Irul\n| extra4 = Sivam\n| length4 = 3:07\n|total_length = 17:34}}\n\n== Marketing ==\nThe first look posters were released on 24 June 2018.<ref name=\"silverscreen\">{{cite web|url=https://silverscreen.in/tamil/news/adanga-maru-jayam-ravi-sports-an-intense-look-in-this-cop-drama/|title=Adanga Maru: Jayam Ravi's Cop Avatar Looks Intense|website=Silverscreen.in|accessdate=31 October 2018|date=25 June 2018}}</ref> The film's teaser was released on 15 August 2018 while trailer was unveiled on 31 October 2018.<ref name=\"indianexpress\">{{cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/adanga-maru-teaser-jayam-ravi-5309229/|title=Adanga Maru teaser: Jayam Ravi is back as the lone-wolf crime fighter|website=The Indian Express|accessdate=31 October 2018|date=16 August 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"indiatimes4\">{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/adanga-maru-trailer-of-the-jayam-ravi-starrer-to-release-on-october-31/articleshow/66409823.cms|title='Adanga Maru': Trailer of the Jayam Ravi starrer to release on October 31 &#124; Tamil Movie News|website=Times of India|accessdate=31 October 2018}}</ref> It was later announced that the film's release that are scheduled to release on 16 November 2018 is postponed to a later date, following [[Tamil Film Producers Council|TFPC]] committee and actor [[Udhaya (actor)|Udhaya]]'s request.<ref name=\"Behindwoods\">{{cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/seethakathi-and-adangamaru-release-postponed.html|title=Seethakathi and Adangamaru release postponed|website=Behindwoods|accessdate=4 November 2018|date=3 November 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Twitter\">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/PROThiyagu/status/1058691164298047488|title=@ACTOR_UDHAYAA thanking the entire team of #Seethakaathi & #Adangamaru for moving release date to later. #UtharavuMaharajafromNOV16|website=Twitter|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Release and reception ==\n''Adanga Maru'' was released on 21 December 2018. Thinkal Menon of ''[[The Times of India]]'' rated it 3 out of 5, saying, \"''Adanga Maru'' has a routine plot, but the treatment makes it fast-paced and interesting.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movie-reviews/adanga-maru/movie-review/67181071.cms |title=Adanga Maru Movie Review |last=Menon |first=Thinkal |date=21 December 2018 |work=[[The Times of India]] |access-date=21 December 2018}}</ref> ''Behindwoods'' wrote \"Adangamaru's fresh screenplay and packaging makes this intense revenge drama, a good watch!\".<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/adanga-maru/adanga-maru-review.html |title = Adanga Maru (Aka) JR 24 review|date = 21 December 2018}}</ref> ''The Hindu'' wrote \"Thanks to its speedy screenplay, Adanga Maru finishes as a fairly engaging watch\".<ref name = hi>{{cite news | url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/reviews/adanga-maru-review-an-engaging-revenge-drama/article25799378.ece | title='Adanga Maru' review: An engaging revenge drama|first=Srinivasa|last=Ramanujam|date=21 December 2018|newspaper=The Hindu|accessdate=24 March 2019}}</ref> ''India Today'' wrote \"Debutant director Karthik Thangavel's Adanga Maru starring Jayam Ravi could have been a flawless cop thriller, but it misses the mark by a few inches\".<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/reviews/story/adanga-maru-movie-review-jayam-ravi-has-a-message-in-this-intense-thriller-1414167-2018-12-21 |title = Adanga Maru Movie Review: Jayam Ravi has a message in this intense thriller}}</ref> ''The Indian Express'' wrote \"A more nuanced, well thought-out storyline with better CGI could have definitely elevated the revenge saga. Adanga Maru is strictly a one-time watch\".<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/adanga-maru-movie-review-jayam-ravi-convincing-engaging-cop-drama-5504566/ | title=Adanga Maru movie review: Jayam Ravi is convincing in the engaging cop drama| date=21 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|tt8364418}}\n\n[[Category:2018 films]]\n[[Category:2010s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:2010s action thriller films]]\n[[Category:2010s police films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian action thriller films]]\n[[Category:Indian police films]]\n[[Category:Indian vigilante films]]\n[[Category:Indian films about revenge]]\n[[Category:Films about rape in India]]\n[[Category:Indian rape and revenge films]]\n[[Category:2018 directorial debut films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2018 Indian Tamil-language action thriller film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Adanga Maru\n| image          = Adanga Maru.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = Karthik Thangavel\n| writer         = \n| screenplay     = Karthik Thangavel\n| story          = Karthik Thangavel\n| studio         = Home Movie Makers\n| starring       = [[Jayam Ravi]]<br />[[Raashi Khanna]]\n| music          = [[Sam C. S.]]\n| distributor    = [[Clap Board Production]]\n| released       = 21 December 2018\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| producer       = Sujatha Vijaykumar\n| editing        = [[Anthony L. Ruben|Ruben]]\n| cinematography = [[Sathyan Sooryan]]\n| runtime        = 146 minutes\n| budget         = <!--Must cite a reliable published source with a reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb. no fan-sites.--> \n| gross          = <!--Must cite a reliable published source with a reputation for fact-checking. No blogs, no IMDb. no fan-sites.--> \n}}\n'''''Adanga Maru''''' ({{trans|Refuse to bow down}}) is a 2018 Indian [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-language [[action film|action]] [[thriller film]] written and directed by Karthik Thangavel in his directorial debut. The film stars [[Jayam Ravi]] and [[Raashi Khanna]] with [[Ponvannan]], [[Ramdoss]], [[Sampath Raj]], [[Mime Gopi]], and [[Azhagam Perumal]] in supporting roles. The score and soundtrack was composed by [[Sam C. S.]], while cinematography and editing was handled by [[Sathyan Sooryan]] and [[Anthony L. Ruben]] respectively. The film began production in December 2017 and released on 21 December 2018.\n\n== Plot ==\nSubhash is an sincere and new Sub-Inspector of Police in Chennai. He resides with his father, mother, elder brother, his wife, and their twin daughters. He is all set to marry his fianc\u00e9e Anitha. He is new to his job and is assisted by Constable Ramadass and SSI Chandran. Subhash cannot stand the suffering of the public and looks for ways to better their lives, and this often lands him in trouble with his superior Inspector Muthukaruppan.\n\nOne day, Chandran and Subhash are called on to investigate the supposed suicide of a girl. On closer investigation, Subhash deduces that it was not a suicide and that she was murdered. While collecting evidence to support this, he comes across a person called Abhijit (Bharath Raj), whose cell number was active near the place. On confronting Abhijit and his friends Christy, Bhuvanesh, and Deepak, they reveal that they are all stoners from affluent families and show a video of them doing drugs, raping and murdering the girl and many other women, as well. Subhash gets enraged, beats them up, and locks them in jail. When his superior, a corrupt Joint Commissioner Saarangan IPS, asks for the proof behind his accusations, he finds out that the phone had automatically deleted all the video files just as he was trying to unlock it. The four are released due to lack of evidence and the influence of their respective fathers and Subhash is suspended. Abhijit and his friends vow revenge and soon enough, when Subhash goes home, he finds his parents and brother's family dead. Only one of his nieces, Anusha, is left alive. Meanwhile, Saarangan is bribed with a Porsche car and reports the murder of Subhash's family as a fire accident at their new house. Dejected at his powerlessness even though he is a police officer, Subhash resigns and threatens Saarangan that he will avenge his family's death and will make sure that the four guys die mercilessly at the hands of their own fathers.\n\nFirst, he kidnaps Bhuvan and locks him in a car with a mechanism that fills silane gas in it if anyone tries to open the door. Bhuvan's father, the district collector, accidentally opens the car door as he searches for his missing son, and Bhuvan is burnt alive in front of his father. Next, he kidnaps Deepak and Christy and keeps them at undisclosed locations. The police, in order to find the missing guys, try to unofficially arrest Subhash at gunpoint, but he triggers Muthukaruppan's pistol on purpose, resulting in his arrest and gaining unwanted public attention. With increasing media and political attention, Saarangan and the rich fathers are unable to carry out extreme measures of interrogation on Subhash, though he is in custody. Subhash then reveals to all of them that he kept Christy in a van and asks him to go to the airport, but Christy's father double crosses Subhash and asks him to run for help, thinking that Christy is safe when police and the public are nearby. Before Christy could do so, an auto-loaded gun in his bag starts beeping, and Christy, assumed to be a terrorist, is brutally shot and killed by the Paramilitary Force (CISF) soldiers to safeguard the public. After this, Deepak is found to be locked in a glass tank connected to harmful chemicals. Subhash and his tech friend expose him as a rapist to the public via an online gaming link, where the public can virtually try to shoot at Deepak in order to release the chemicals into the tank and eventually kill him. His father hires hackers to stop this, and when Deepak's location is found, he goes there and breaks open the tank to release him, but the chemicals instantly blow up, and he is killed. Meanwhile, Subhash also threatens Saarangan to check on his teenage daughter's safety. Saarangan panics but is relieved when she is found to be safe. Saarangan realizes his mistake and decides to support Subhash in his fight for justice to the rape and murder victims.\n\nNow that only Abhijit is left, his father Sanjay, a business tycoon, decides to release Subhash from custody and deal with him alone. Subhash tactfully kidnaps Abhijit and has him hanging on a rope. He also threatens to upload the video evidence online and expose their crimes, thereby bringing Sanjay's business empire down. He gives Sanjay an ultimatum that he could either hold on to the rope and save his son or let go and shut down the laptop instead, to save his reputation. In the end, the power-hungry Sanjay decides to save his reputation and lets go of the rope, killing Abhijit.\n\nOne year later, Subhash has become a peace-loving IPS officer, who murders criminals out of record to serve justice.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin}}\n*[[Jayam Ravi]] as S. Subash\n*[[Raashi Khanna]] as Anitha\n*[[Sampath Raj]] as J. C. P. Sarangan\n*[[Ramdoss]] as Constable Ramadass\n*[[Ponvannan]] as Subash's father\n*[[Azhagam Perumal]] as SI Chandran\n*[[Mime Gopi]] as Inspector Muthukarappan\n*Bharat Raj as Abhijit\n*[[Shabeer Kallarakkal]] as Bhuvanesh (Bhuvan)\n*[[Sriranjini (Tamil actress)|Sriranjini]] as Subash's mother\n*[[Subbu Panchu]] as Subash's brother\n*[[Meera Vasudevan]] as Subash's sister-in-law\n*[[Babu Antony]] as Sanjay, Abhijit's father\n*Dithi as Anusha\n*Dishi as Vinusha\n*[[Chaams]] as Drunkard\n*[[Shamna Kasim|Poorna]] as Subash's lawyer (guest appearance)<ref name=\"indiatimes\">{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/poorna-is-a-lawyer-in-adanga-maru/articleshow/65307050.cms|title=Poorna is a lawyer in Adanga Maru &#124; Tamil Movie News|website=Times of India|accessdate=31 October 2018}}</ref>\n*Mathew Varghese as a rich man\n*RJ Sindhu (special appearance in the song \"Aangu Vaangu\")\n*VJ Syed (special appearance in the song \"Aangu Vaangu\")\n{{colend}}\n\n== Production ==\nIn December 2017, Jayam Ravi announced on social media that his 23rd film will be an action-thriller titled ''Adanga Maru'' by debutant Karthik Thangavel.<ref name=\"firstpost\">{{cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/adanga-maru-jayam-ravi-announces-title-of-his-next-film-will-go-on-floors-on-14-december-4257997.html|title=Adanga Maru: Jayam Ravi announces title of his next film, will go on floors on 14 December- Entertainment News, Firstpost|website=firstpost.com|accessdate=31 October 2018|date=14 December 2017}}</ref> Stunt choreographer [[Stun Siva]]'s son, Kevin Kumar made his debut as stunt choreographer with this film.<ref name=\"indiatimes2\">{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/stun-sivas-son-gets-his-own-fight-sequence/articleshow/65164764.cms|title=Stun Siva's son gets his own fight sequence &#124; Tamil Movie News|website=Times of India|accessdate=31 October 2018}}</ref> Filming was completed in May 2018.<ref name=\"indiatimes3\">{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/jayam-ravis-adanga-maru-is-almost-complete/articleshow/64260440.cms|title=Jayam Ravi's 'Adanga Maru' is almost complete &#124; Tamil Movie News|website=Times of India|accessdate=31 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Soundtrack ==\nThe soundtrack was composed by [[Sam C. S.]]<ref name=\"saavn\">{{cite web|url=https://www.saavn.com/album/adanga-maru/SEe-AFCXq9Y_|title=Adanga Maru - All Songs - Download or Listen Free Online|website=Saavn|accessdate=31 October 2018}}</ref> The Audio Rights was bagged by [[Sony Music India|Sony Music]] in end of August 2018.\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Adanga Maru\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Sam C. S.]]\n| cover      = \n| alt        =\n| released   = 2018\n| recorded   =\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = Tamil\n| length     = 17:34\n| language   = Tamil\n| label      = [[Sony Music India|Sony Music]]\n| producer   = Sam C. S.\n| prev_title = [[Lakshmi (2018 film)|Lakshmi]]\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| next_title = [[Vanjagar Ulagam]]\n| next_year  = 2018\n}}\n{{tracklist\n| extra_column =Singers\n| title1 = Aangu Vaangu\n| extra1 = Sam C. S., Mukesh, [[M. L. R. Karthikeyan]]\n| length1 = 4:26\n| title2 = Saayaali\n| extra2 = Sathyaprakash, [[Chinmayi]]\n| length2 = 5:15\n| title3 = Pachai Dhrogangal\n| extra3 = [[Haricharan]]\n| length3 = 3:46\n| title4 = Kaar Irul\n| extra4 = Sivam\n| length4 = 3:07\n|total_length = 17:34}}\n\n== Marketing ==\nThe first look posters were released on 24 June 2018.<ref name=\"silverscreen\">{{cite web|url=https://silverscreen.in/tamil/news/adanga-maru-jayam-ravi-sports-an-intense-look-in-this-cop-drama/|title=Adanga Maru: Jayam Ravi's Cop Avatar Looks Intense|website=Silverscreen.in|accessdate=31 October 2018|date=25 June 2018}}</ref> The film's teaser was released on 15 August 2018 while trailer was unveiled on 31 October 2018.<ref name=\"indianexpress\">{{cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/adanga-maru-teaser-jayam-ravi-5309229/|title=Adanga Maru teaser: Jayam Ravi is back as the lone-wolf crime fighter|website=The Indian Express|accessdate=31 October 2018|date=16 August 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"indiatimes4\">{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/adanga-maru-trailer-of-the-jayam-ravi-starrer-to-release-on-october-31/articleshow/66409823.cms|title='Adanga Maru': Trailer of the Jayam Ravi starrer to release on October 31 &#124; Tamil Movie News|website=Times of India|accessdate=31 October 2018}}</ref> It was later announced that the film's release that are scheduled to release on 16 November 2018 is postponed to a later date, following [[Tamil Film Producers Council|TFPC]] committee and actor [[Udhaya (actor)|Udhaya]]'s request.<ref name=\"Behindwoods\">{{cite web|url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-cinema-news-16/seethakathi-and-adangamaru-release-postponed.html|title=Seethakathi and Adangamaru release postponed|website=Behindwoods|accessdate=4 November 2018|date=3 November 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"Twitter\">{{cite web|url=https://twitter.com/PROThiyagu/status/1058691164298047488|title=@ACTOR_UDHAYAA thanking the entire team of #Seethakaathi & #Adangamaru for moving release date to later. #UtharavuMaharajafromNOV16|website=Twitter|accessdate=4 November 2018}}</ref>\n\n== Release and reception ==\n''Adanga Maru'' was released on 21 December 2018. Thinkal Menon of ''[[The Times of India]]'' rated it 3 out of 5, saying, \"''Adanga Maru'' has a routine plot, but the treatment makes it fast-paced and interesting.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movie-reviews/adanga-maru/movie-review/67181071.cms |title=Adanga Maru Movie Review |last=Menon |first=Thinkal |date=21 December 2018 |work=[[The Times of India]] |access-date=21 December 2018}}</ref> ''Behindwoods'' wrote \"Adangamaru's fresh screenplay and packaging makes this intense revenge drama, a good watch!\".<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/adanga-maru/adanga-maru-review.html |title = Adanga Maru (Aka) JR 24 review|date = 21 December 2018}}</ref> ''The Hindu'' wrote \"Thanks to its speedy screenplay, Adanga Maru finishes as a fairly engaging watch\".<ref name = hi>{{cite news | url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/reviews/adanga-maru-review-an-engaging-revenge-drama/article25799378.ece | title='Adanga Maru' review: An engaging revenge drama|first=Srinivasa|last=Ramanujam|date=21 December 2018|newspaper=The Hindu|accessdate=24 March 2019}}</ref> ''India Today'' wrote \"Debutant director Karthik Thangavel's Adanga Maru starring Jayam Ravi could have been a flawless cop thriller, but it misses the mark by a few inches\".<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.indiatoday.in/movies/reviews/story/adanga-maru-movie-review-jayam-ravi-has-a-message-in-this-intense-thriller-1414167-2018-12-21 |title = Adanga Maru Movie Review: Jayam Ravi has a message in this intense thriller}}</ref> ''The Indian Express'' wrote \"A more nuanced, well thought-out storyline with better CGI could have definitely elevated the revenge saga. Adanga Maru is strictly a one-time watch\".<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/movie-review/adanga-maru-movie-review-jayam-ravi-convincing-engaging-cop-drama-5504566/ | title=Adanga Maru movie review: Jayam Ravi is convincing in the engaging cop drama| date=21 December 2018}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|tt8364418}}\n\n[[Category:2018 films]]\n[[Category:2010s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:2010s action thriller films]]\n[[Category:2010s police films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian action thriller films]]\n[[Category:Indian police films]]\n[[Category:Indian vigilante films]]\n[[Category:Indian films about revenge]]\n[[Category:Films about rape in India]]\n[[Category:Indian rape and revenge films]]\n[[Category:2018 directorial debut films]]\n", "name_user": "2402:3a80:44e:685f:0:5d:ac4b:bf01", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eCast)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adanga_Maru"}
